OL,4,Cfireworks thrown by youths set home on
OL,5,Cfire
OL,7,F"I was watching telly in the living
OL,8,Froom and one of our neighbours came
OL,9,Fbanging on our door," he said.
OL,11,F"He said 'your back garden's on fire'.
OL,12,FI turned around barefoot and ran to
OL,13,Fthe back, the flames were as high as
OL,14,Fthe house.
OL,16,F"I got a hosepipe and started hosing
OL,17,Fthe fire before the fire brigade got
OL,18,Fthere. It was like an inferno, our
OL,19,Fnext door neighbour's garden went up
OL,20,Fas well.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/6
